  "id": "d1f1e058-52fb-51bf-a454-4359b13bea4f",
  "slug": "how-to-make-the-perfect-rice-puff-dessert",
  "name": "Perfect Rice Puff Dessert",
  "recipe_type": "dessert",
  "brief_description": "Chocolate Rice puff or popped rice are grains of rice that are popped and dehydrated. This is often mixed with sweeteners such as sugar or corn syrup and eaten as breakfast cereals. There is a popular snack in the Philippines called \u201campaw\u201d which is made from sweetened popped rice.I\u2019m not planning to post a recipe using rice puffs until I noticed several open boxes of puffed rice cereals that my kids eat during breakfast.",
  "cuisine": null,
  "instructions": [
    {
      "position": 1,
      "text": "Heat a large sauce pan then put-in the butter and allow it to melt."
    },
    {
      "position": 2,
      "text": "Once the butter melts, add the light corn syrup and brown sugar then stir to distribute the ingredients."
    },
    {
      "position": 3,
      "text": "When the mixture starts to boil, add the rice puffs then mix well until the rice puffs are completely coated with the liquid mixture."
    },
    {
      "position": 4,
      "text": "Turn off the heat then allow the rice puffs to cool down."
    },
    {
      "position": 5,
      "text": "Wet your hands then scoop about \u00bc cup of rice puff mixture then mold into a ball shape figure."
    },
    {
      "position": 6,
      "text": "Place in a serving plate then serve. Share and enjoy!"
    }
  ],
  "servings": 4,
